<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/T4/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div>
<div class="tw-foot p"><div class="fn" id="fn2"><p>Two thresholds with nearly identical Youden J statistic were
identified for the cohort of patients with <em>C.
acnes-</em>positive cultures; ICM = International
Consensus Meeting; NPV = negative predictive value; PPV =
positive predictive value; AUC = area under the curve.</p></div></div></section></section><section id="s3-3"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">Using D-Dimer in Combination with Other Serum Tests</h3>
<p>In assessing the serum tests for diagnostic accuracy when used in combination, we
used the calculated thresholds from the ROC analysis of D-dimer (598 ng/mL), ESR
(28 mm/hour), and CRP (0.7 mg/dL). The specificity of detecting PJI (88%) was
high when three positive serum markers (ESR, CRP, and D-dimer) were required, at
the expense of sensitivity (28%; Table <a href="#T5" class="usa-link">5</a>). The overall testing accuracy and specificity were highest when using
D-dimer in combination with ESR, CRP, or both.</p>
<section class="tw xbox font-sm" id="T5"><h4 class="obj_head">Table 5.</h4>
